{"id": "d0962d72a96a", "type": "Gym", "date": "2026-06-18", "dur": 45.0, "dist": 0.0, "note": "Strength training. Solid lifting session.", "source": "manual", "ext_id": ""}], "tasks": [{"id": "056a03d90b49", "name": "Submit Database Assignment 3", "done": 0, "created": "2026-06-15", "completed_at": null, "due": "2026-06-15T23:59", "category": "School", "order_index": 0, "due_date": "2026-06-15", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "ed733d91e4a2", "name": "Review dynamic programming notes", "done": 1, "created": "2026-06-16", "completed_at": "2026-06-16", "due": "2026-06-16T15:00", "category": "School", "order_index": 1, "due_date": "2026-06-16", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "9a39beb21de1", "name": "Prepare presentation slides", "done": 1, "created": "2026-06-18", "completed_at": "2026-06-19", "due": "2026-06-19T14:00", "category": "School", "order_index": 0, "due_date": "2026-06-19", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "50cd873e19e3", "name": "Implement Web Push service worker", "done": 1, "created": "2026-06-19", "completed_at": "2026-06-19", "due": "2026-06-19T17:00", "category": "School", "order_index": 2, "due_date": "2026-06-19", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "115bf9aabdf5", "name": "Draft thesis project proposal", "done": 0, "created": "2026-06-19", "completed_at": null, "due": "2026-06-23T12:00", "category": "School", "order_index": 3, "due_date": "2026-06-23", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "c0c86a7e333b", "name": "Complete algorithms homework sheet 5", "done": 0, "created": "2026-06-19", "completed_at": null, "due": "2026-06-25T23:59", "category": "School", "order_index": 4, "due_date": "2026-06-25", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "605796c66923", "name": "Bugfix: resolve timezone offsets in ICS export", "done": 1, "created": "2026-06-17", "completed_at": "2026-06-18", "due": "", "category": "Work", "order_index": 0, "due_date": "2026-06-18", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "caa412902c35", "name": "Update team board sprint metrics", "done": 0, "created": "2026-06-19", "completed_at": null, "due": "2026-06-24T18:00", "category": "Work", "order_index": 1, "due_date": "2026-06-24", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "c76d902b5561", "name": "Buy milk, eggs, and bread", "done": 0, "created": "2026-06-19", "completed_at": null, "due": "2026-06-19T18:00", "category": "Personal", "order_index": 0, "due_date": "2026-06-19", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "a97caed84407", "name": "Organize computer desk and files", "done": 0, "created": "2026-06-19", "completed_at": null, "due": "2026-06-21T12:00", "category": "Personal", "order_index": 1, "due_date": "2026-06-21", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "c8a6904710f6", "name": "Schedule dentist appointment", "done": 0, "created": "2026-06-19", "completed_at": null, "due": "", "category": "Personal", "order_index": 2, "due_date": "", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "b8e0781a8d30", "name": "Plan weekend bike route", "done": 1, "created": "2026-06-19", "completed_at": "2026-06-19", "due": "", "category": "Personal", "order_index": 3, "due_date": "2026-06-19", "parent_id": null}, {"id": "ba8ad61c1ec1", "name": "Renew university library books", "done": 0, "created": "2026-06-19", "completed_at": null, "due": "2026-06-22T09:00", "category": "Personal", "order_index": 4, "due_date": "2026-06-22", "parent_id": null}], "notes": [{"id": "n1", "title": "Wiki Index", "body": "# Wiki Index \ud83d\udcc1\n\nWelcome to your TyloPlanner workspace!\n\n## Quick Navigation\n- [[Study Guide]] - Formula sheets & exam prep notes\n- [[Project Ideas]] - Creative coding side projects\n- [[Personal Backlog]] - Life admin tasks and goals\n- [[Strava API Integration]] - OAuth flow details\n\n---\n*Last updated: Today*", "updated": 1686940000, "is_pinned": 1}, {"id": "n2", "title": "Study Guide", "body": "# Study Guide: Algorithms & Complexity\n\n## Dynamic Programming Formulas\n- Fibonacci numbers: $F(n) = F(n-1) + F(n-2)$\n- Knapsack recurrence:\n  $$DP[i][w] = \\max(DP[i-1][w], DP[i-1][w-w_i] + v_i)$$\n\n## Sorting Complexity Table\n| Algorithm | Time (Best) | Time (Worst) | Space |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Quicksort | $O(N \\log N)$ | $O(N^2)$ | $O(\\log N)$ |\n| Mergesort | $O(N \\log N)$ | $O(N \\log N)$ | $O(N)$ |\n| Heapsort  | $O(N \\log N)$ | $O(N \\log N)$ | $O(1)$ |\n\n## Big-O Notation Cheat Sheet\n- **Constant**: $O(1)$ (e.g. array lookup)\n- **Logarithmic**: $O(\\log N)$ (e.g. binary search)\n- **Linear**: $O(N)$ (e.g. simple traversal)\n- **Linearithmic**: $O(N \\log N)$ (e.g. merge sort)\n- **Quadratic**: $O(N^2)$ (e.g. bubble sort)\n", "updated": 1686941000, "is_pinned": 0}, {"id": "n3", "title": "Project Ideas", "body": "# Project Ideas \ud83d\udca1\n\n- **TyloPlanner Mobile Companion:** React Native wrapper for PWA\n- **Smart Fridge Tracker:** OCR scanner for grocery receipts\n- **Auto-Summarizer CLI:** LLM script to compress research papers\n- **Personal Finance Dashboard:** Automatic bank statement parser & charts", "updated": 1686942000, "is_pinned": 0}, {"id": "n4", "title": "Strava API Integration", "body": "# Strava API Integration Notes \ud83d\udeb4\n\nHere are the details for setting up the webhook and authentication token exchange.\n\n## Authentication Flow\n1. Redirect user to Strava authorization URL:\n   `https://www.strava.com/oauth/authorize?client_id=CLIENT_ID&redirect_uri=REDIRECT&response_type=code&scope=activity:read_all`\n2. Exchange code for access token:\n   `POST https://www.strava.com/oauth/token`\n3. Refresh token when expired (`expires_at` timestamp check).\n\n## API Endpoints Used\n- `/athlete/activities` - Fetch logged athlete workouts.\n- `/activities/{id}` - Retrieve detailed GPX/map stream details.\n", "updated": 1686942500, "is_pinned": 0}, {"id": "n5", "title": "Weekly Groceries", "body": "# Weekly Groceries \ud83d\uded2\n\n- [x] Spinach & Kale\n- [x] Eggs (dozen)\n- [ ] Milk (oat)\n- [ ] Whole wheat bread\n- [ ] Greek yogurt\n- [ ] Coffee beans\n- [ ] Chicken breast (1kg)", "updated": 1686942600, "is_pinned": 0}, {"id": "899d68c2689d", "title": "How to use Notes", "body": "# How to use Notes\n\nWelcome! Here is everything the Notes section can do.\n\n---\n\n## Writing & saving\n\nType in the editor \u2014 your note **saves automatically** in the background. A live save status indicator (e.g. *Typing...*, *Saving...*, or *Saved at HH:MM:SS*) is displayed in the header alongside word and character counters.\n\n## Read Mode & Split View\n\nYou can customize the layout of the editor using the control toggles:\n- **Read Mode** (pill slider in the header) \u2014 When turned **ON**, it hides the editing area and toolbar, displaying the clean, formatted note along with the search bar.\n- **Split View** (checkmark toggle in the toolbar) \u2014 When Read Mode is **OFF**, toggle Split View to switch between a side-by-side editing layout (Split) or a distraction-free editor-only layout.\n\nLayout toggle states are saved automatically **per note** and persist across page reloads.\n\n## Searching within notes\n\nUse the search bar at the bottom of the header to search for text inside the current note.\n- All matching text will be highlighted in yellow.\n- Use the **\u2191** and **\u2193** arrows, or simply press **Enter** in the search box, to step through each result.\n- The search bar takes up the full width of the editor and is styled slightly larger in **Read Mode** for readability.\n- It is fully active in both editing layouts and in **Read Mode**.\n\n---\n\n## Formatting toolbar\n\nThe toolbar above the text area inserts Markdown at your cursor position. Select text first, then click a formatting button to wrap the selection:\n\n- **B** \u2014 bold: `**text**`\n- **I** \u2014 italic: `*text*`\n- **H1** \u2014 heading: `# text`\n- **\u2022 List** \u2014 bullet item: `- text`\n- **1. List** \u2014 numbered item: `1. text`\n- **\u2014** \u2014 horizontal divider: `---`\n\n---\n\n## Markdown reference\n\n# Heading 1\n## Heading 2\n### Heading 3\n\n**bold text** and *italic text* and ~~strikethrough~~\n\n> This is a blockquote. Great for callouts or quotes.\n\n- Bullet one\n- Bullet two\n\n1. Step one\n2. Step two\n\n---\n\n## Linking to other notes\n\nType `[[Note Title]]` anywhere to create a clickable cross-reference.\n\n- If the note **exists**: the link turns blue and opens that note when clicked.\n- If the note **does not exist yet**: the link appears grey with a dashed underline.\n- Titles are matched **case-insensitively**, so `[[my note]]` and `[[My Note]]` both work.\n\n*This note can be edited or deleted at any time \u2014 it will not come back.*\n", "updated": 1781900498780, "is_pinned": 0}], "files": [{"id": "fil1", "filename": "database_syllabus.pdf", "size": 1024350, "mimetype": "application/pdf", "uploaded": 1686943000, "is_pinned": 1, "folder_id": "fld1"}, {"id": "fil2", "filename": "algorithms_intro.pdf", "size": 4502000, "mimetype": "application/pdf", "uploaded": 1686944000, "is_pinned": 0, "folder_id": "fld1"}, {"id": "fil3", "filename": "web_security_cheatsheet.pdf", "size": 521400, "mimetype": "application/pdf", "uploaded": 1686944200, "is_pinned": 0, "folder_id": "fld1"}, {"id": "fil4", "filename": "programming_task_1.py", "size": 12300, "mimetype": "text/x-python", "uploaded": 1686944300, "is_pinned": 0, "folder_id": "fld2"}, {"id": "fil5", "filename": "project_report_draft.docx", "size": 245000, "mimetype": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document", "uploaded": 1686944400, "is_pinned": 0, "folder_id": "fld2"}, {"id": "fil6", "filename": "web_push_notifications_spec.pdf", "size": 890000, "mimetype": "application/pdf", "uploaded": 1686944500, "is_pinned": 0, "folder_id": "fld3"}, {"id": "fil7", "filename": "indexeddb_offline_sync_paper.pdf", "size": 1200000, "mimetype": "application/pdf", "uploaded": 1686944600, "is_pinned": 0, "folder_id": "fld3"}, {"id": "fil8", "filename": "thesis_proposal_final.pdf", "size": 1520300, "mimetype": "application/pdf", "uploaded": 1686945000, "is_pinned": 1, "folder_id": null}, {"id": "fil9", "filename": "avatar_profile_pic.png", "s